.TH "ti_sci_get_one_xfer" 9 "ti_sci_get_one_xfer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ti_sci_get_one_xfer \- Allocate one message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ti_sci_xfer *" ti_sci_get_one_xfer
.BI "(struct ti_sci_info *info "  ","
.BI "u16 msg_type "  ","
.BI "u32 msg_flags "  ","
.BI "size_t tx_message_size "  ","
.BI "size_t rx_message_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
Pointer to SCI entity information
.IP "msg_type" 12
Message type
.IP "msg_flags" 12
Flag to set for the message
.IP "tx_message_size" 12
transmit message size
.IP "rx_message_size" 12
receive message size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Helper function which is used by various command functions that are
exposed to clients of this driver for allocating a message traffic event.

This function can sleep depending on pending requests already in the system
for the SCI entity. Further, this also holds a spinlock to maintain integrity
of internal data structures.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if all went fine, else corresponding error.
